INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L155$$, 2026, $$Battle Stations-21 (BST-21): Located at Recruit Training Command Great Lakes, Illinois, Battle Stations-21 (BST-21) provides an unparalleled, realistic training environment aboard a 210-foot-long Arleigh Burke-
 class destroyer. This culminating event immerses recruits in demanding scenarios, ensuring they are prepared for the challenges of serving in the United States Navy. OPN funding aids in the replacement of
 worn, outdated, or obsolete equipment and technology, termed life-cycle replacement, ensuring the training device remains a relevant and effective training tool. The findings of the February 2015 Life-Cycle
 Sustainment assessment continue to be relevant today, highlighting the ongoing need for upgrades in Information Assurance/Cybersecurity and Tech Refresh/Upgrades identified by Naval Air Warfare Training
 Support Division (NAWCTSD).

 The training focuses on key shipboard skills through realistic simulations, complete with authentic sounds, sights, and smells. This includes: shipboard line handling and stores onloading, missile strikes, mass
 casualty scenarios with medical response and extraction of distressed manikins, realistic watch standing exercises involving navigation, radar contact identification, engineering equipment monitoring, security
 sentry duties, and space identification, emergency egress procedures, a flooding event where recruits work as a team to identify and mitigate flooding in a confined space, a man overboard event, and a live
 firefighting event where recruits, in a coordinated team effort, don firefighting equipment and engage a controlled live fire.

 Commander, Naval Education and Training Command stated "BST-21 is a mandatory graduation requirement and a Fleet requirement for Block 0 of the Ready, Relevant Learning initiative," marking the
 completion of the first step in their journey from civilian to sailor, and future Naval enlisted warfighter, in the United States Navy.

 Small Arms Marksmanship Training Device (SAM-T): Located at Recruit Training Command Great Lakes, Illinois, The Small Arms Marksmanship Training Device (SAM-T) requires a technology refresh to align
 with the Navy's transition from the M9 to the M18 handgun and support current qualification standards. The acquisition enables full use of 60 firing lanes, doubling throughput, and enhancing training realism prior
 to a live-fire qualification event. Funding the technology refresh of the SAM-T ensures Recruits train on the same platform used in live-fire, improving readiness and qualification success rates while maintaining
 compliance with OPNAVINST 3591.1G and DoW Cybersecurity requirements.

 [P40A / BST-21 AUDIOVISUAL LIGHTING SYSTEMS]: Funding provided for updates to Audiovisual Lighting Systems to train recruits.

 [P40A / BST-21 SUPPORT SYSTEM]: Funding also provides for upgrades to operating equipment, software modifications, and UPS subsystem; ocean fill valve, pit sump pumps Variable Frequency Drive (VFD)
 controllers, blocking valve (natural gas) and power panel, pier stores, and tour brief station.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
