 new, an upgraded model, or recapitalized production items from the manufacturer's plant or source of procurement to the first point of delivery where the Military Service or Defense Agency takes possession and/
 or ownership of that item. The procurement source, as used herein, is any supplier outside the DoW supply system or any DoW industrial activity that fabricates new materiel. The procurement source or the first
 point of delivery may be in the Continental United States (CONUS) or overseas."$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Army                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
