 Supplemental (P.L. 118-50, Division A., Sec. 101). Both ammunition are fired from MK 45 gun installed on Cruiser and Destroyer combatant ships against air, surface, and shore targets. Conventional 5"/54
 Ammunition items procured includes propelling charges, high-explosive projectiles, fuzes, and training rounds.

 In FY 2024 the USN 5"/54 ammunition production was line was shut down due to the production facility eliminating their 5"/54 ammunition production capability in support of the Ukraine requirement for 155mm
 ammunition. As a result, the USN 5"/54 ammunition inventory is critically low and will worsen if action is not taken immediately.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
