INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1109_L067$$, 2027, $$This budget line item includes various procurements such as engineering efforts, engineering change proposals, modifications, and other related items less than $5 million each.

 Family of Shelters and Shelters Equipment (FSSE) provides expeditionary soft wall shelters, rigid wall shelters, and camouflage netting to protect personnel from environmental effects and conceals personnel
 and equipment from detection. The various expeditionary shelters, heater, and lighting system serve as berthing quarters, command posts, and ground equipment maintenance shops in support of Marines
 operating in expeditionary environments. The next generation Ultra Lightweight Camouflage Netting System (ULCANS) directly supports Force Design by providing enhanced spectrum compliance in concealing
 high value targets through signature management and reducing detection and observation.

 The Family of Expeditionary Water Systems (FEWS) provides complementary bulk, modular, small unit, and individual water purification, distribution, and hygiene capabilities. These land-based systems perform
 water analysis, purification, storage, and distribution of potable water while delivering hygiene services to Marine Corps units. FEWS systems are expeditionary and configurable to mission requirements, enabling
 combat operations by providing purified drinking water from fresh, brackish, and saltwater sources to warfighters, medical organizations, and food service formations within the MLR while reducing Class I (w)
 logistics resupply requirements. The Family of Hygiene Equipment delivers modern sanitation standards for Role 2 medical, mortuary affairs, and food service missions while minimizing logistics burden during
 Large-Scale Combat Operations (LSCO).

 Engineer Modification Kits (EMK) and Tool Kits enhance equipment capabilities, expand protection, and enable operations in Expeditionary Advanced Base Operations (EABO) and Littoral Operations in
 Contested Environments (LOCE). They provide direct/indirect fire protection and mission-specific tools for Force Modernization. Supporting 47,000+ engineer systems across 120 TAMCNs, EMK enables
 equipment armor installations, upgrades, and safety modifications for legacy and new systems while providing quick response capability for Fleet Marine Force sustainment, safety engineering, readiness, and
 Quality Deficiency Report analysis.

