INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1506_L008$$, 2026, $$The V-22 is a tilt-rotor vertical takeoff and landing aircraft currently being produced for joint service application. The program provides an aircraft to meet the amphibious/vertical assault needs of the United
 States Marine Corps (USMC), the Carrier Onboard Delivery (COD) needs of the United States Navy (USN), and supplements United States Special Operations Command (USSOCOM) special mission aircraft.
 The aircraft is capable of flying 2,100 miles with one refueling, and gives the Services the advantage of a Vertical/Short Takeoff and Landing (V/STOL) aircraft that can rapidly self-deploy to any location in the
 world.

 The current procurement objective is 359 MV-22 USMC aircraft, 53 CMV-22 USN aircraft, and 56 CV-22 aircraft for USSOCOM (funded by USSOCOM and the United States Air Force). The MV-22 program
 successfully completed Milestone III in the 1st Quarter of 2006, and Initial Operational Capability (IOC) in March of 2007. The CMV-22 program successfully completed IOC December of 2021.

 The USMC Program of Record (POR) for MV-22 aircraft quantities is 359. The USN POR for CMV-22 aircraft quantities remains 48. FY24 authorized for five CMV-22 USN aircraft above the program of record.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                      Date: April 2026
