INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1506_L054$$, 2026, $$OSIP 009-18 provides funding to upgrade Baseline aircraft and associated ground stations, including Main and Forward Operating Bases (MOB/FOB) and the stand-alone training MOB, to the IFC-4 configuration
 consisting of the addition of a K-BAR docking station, new Mission Execution equipment that replaces existing payload hardware, upgraded communication and network equipment, and the integration of a
 Cross-Domain Solution (CDS) and other related systems. The technical retrofits for the unmanned aircraft include Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) antennas, a new High Gain Common Data Link (CDL) antenna
 with associated avionics, a Keyed Broad Area Maritime Surveillance Airborne Recorder (K-BAR), and a new Airborne Mission Processor. Further enhancements involve new airborne network hardware,
 high-assurance internet protocol encryptors (HAIPE), new Voice Communications, a Cross Domain Solution (CDS), GPS improvements (M-Code, LN-251 INS/GPS), and airframe modifications to mitigate
 Electromagnetic Interference (EMI). This OSIP also funds the upgrade of training devices from Increment 1 to Increment 2 (IFC-4) and subsequent capability modifications into the training systems that mirror
 the MQ-4C payloads, including but not limited to: MFAS radar, EO/IR systems, ESM, SIGINT, High and Low Band payloads, Remote Quick Look (RQL), Higher Than Secret (HTS) payloads, High Gain Aperture
 (HGA), and maintenance device updates.

 This OSIP also provides funding for MQ-4C Triton payload upgrades to Increment 2, enabling mission system modifications to improve the Multi-Function Active Sensor (MFAS) Radar, electro-optical/infrared
 (EO/IR) systems, Automatic Information Systems (AIS), and Signals Intelligence (SIGINT), High and Low Band payloads, RQL, HTS payloads, HGA, and maintenance device updates. These enhancements
 include the production of payload Weapon Replaceable Assemblies (WRAs) to keep pace with technology insertions. The funding also addresses reliability, maintainability, and suitability degradation in MQ-4C
 payloads and related systems. Furthermore, it supports modernization requirements through DMSMS and engineering changes, as well as necessary upgrades for related training systems. While integration of
 already-qualified airborne systems is the primary approach, ruggedization of COTS/GOTS fielded systems may be pursued if required.

 Development Status/Major Development Milestones: Triton declared Increment 1 Initial Operational Capability (IOC) in July 2023.

 Increase of $30,994K in OSIP 009-18 is in support the maturation and consolidation for the current program budget. This adjustment provides a clearer distinction between the procurement of kits, modifications
 (Engineering Change Proposals), and installations by organizing them according to similar requirements. The FY2027 budget submission includes the consolidation of OSIP 003-26 into OSIP 009-18. This
 consolidation will move all Increment 2 funding for kits, installs, and any required support under a single OSIP thus allowing for a seamless transition of funding and a sustained level of effort to ensure a smooth
 integration of capability for Increment 1 & 2.

 OSIP Consolidation Adjustments:
 CE 1.1.3 EO/IR Upgrade A-kit - New CE
